elements.name: As a new user, I want to be able to create an account so that I can access the Planetarium
elements.description: Users should be able to input a username and password to create an account. The system should validate that the username is unique and that both username and password are under 30 characters.

steps.name: The user is on the Planetarium login page
The user clicks on the create an account button
The user enters "!\"#$%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[]^_`|\~" as a new username
The user enters "!\"#$%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[]^_`|\~" as a new password
The user clicks the Create button
The user should be informed that the account creation was successful

elements.name: As a user, I want to be able to delete moons from the planetarium using their names so that the correct moon will be removed from the planetarium
elements.description: System should only remove the moon with the associated name.

steps.name: The user is logged in
user clicks on the delete text entry field
User enters "Luna" as the moon name
User clicks on the delete moon button
That moon should be deleted from the Planetarium
